element.name: Clarabel & Me by cincol & Clarabel, Traditional Cache (1.5/1.5)
element.description: A small cache located in "Windsocker Country" in the beautiful grounds of Newbridge House.

long-description.p: Newbridge House & Demesne, Donabate was built in 1736 for Archbishop Cobbe. Original furniture, paintings and objets d'art are a feature of this gracious Georgian house. The extensive 150h demesne includes a walled garden, a wildlife and Deer Park, playing and walking areas and a 19th Century working farm, where animals, machinery and old farming techniques are on view.
Park in the official car park.

Alternatively, If you want to do this cache by train: enter the park by the entrance at coordinates N53:29.109, W006:09.275 (very close to the Donabate train station; get a train from Connolly, Tara Street or Pearse Street station in Dublin). To do this cache by bus, take the 33B bus from Swords or Dublin City Centre, which will drop you off at the main entrance to the park (look for sign "Newbridge House and Demesne").
[Note on Cache Maintenance: This cache will be maintained by a local resident and the details are on file with Geocaching.com]

element.encoded-hints: Use your eyes, not your feet.

ul.li:
2010-06-07T19:00:00Z : Found it by niallk1234
Easy find, the second of 6 for today. The demense was packed with muggles for the bank holiday, but there were none in this particular part. People were even having barbeques even though the weather wasn't what you would call ideal! TFTC

2010-05-09T19:00:00Z : Found it by Crannyn
This was our second attempt only because yesterday our iphone ran out of battery! How annoying as we were only a few meters away.Bumped into our friends 'Fitzet' they were at the begining of the 'multi'.Left them to it as we had dinner waiting with the 'in laws' on the southside! TFTC

2010-05-09T19:00:00Z : Found it by Fitzet
GPS was acting up a bit so we ended up having a bit of a detour on the way to find this one. Once we were actually in the right place it was an easy find.
In GC and Bride finger puppet Out mini playing cards
SL TFTC

2010-04-03T19:00:00Z : Found it by daviddotshaw
Found it, This is a nice simple cache, nice part of the park., but today was very wet and you would have needed wellies.
Left - Mini Pack of Card Took - Bouncy ball

2010-03-28T19:00:00Z : Found it by Petr Skacha
Found after little search.[:D] TFTC
